ADVANCED & EXTRA FILE MANAGEMENT COMMANDS
# 1. Create a file with content directly
echo "Hello World" > file.txt


Use: Quickly create config files, scripts, notes.

# 2. Append (add text) to a file
echo "New line" >> file.txt
Adds text without replacing old content.

# 3. Create multiple files at once
touch file1.txt file2.txt file3.txt

# 4. Create multiple numbered files
touch log_{1..10}.txt
Creates:

log_1.txt
log_2.txt
...
log_10.txt
Useful for testing.

# 5. Copy only newer files
cp -u source/ dest/
Prevents overwriting newer files.

# 6. Show the top 20 lines
head -20 file.txt

# 7. Show last 20 lines
tail -20 file.txt

# 8. Monitor a file in real-time (LIVE LOGS)
tail -f /var/log/messages

# 9. Count lines, words, characters
wc file.txt

Or individually:

wc -l file.txt   # lines
wc -w file.txt   # words
wc -c file.txt   # characters

# 10. Compare two files
diff file1.txt file2.txt
Shows differences — useful for config changes.

# 11. Compress a folder
tar -czvf backup.tar.gz foldername/

# 12. Extract a tar file
tar -xzvf backup.tar.gz

# 13. Delete files older than 7 days
find /tmp -type f -mtime +7 -delete


Real world: clean old logs.

# 14. Find and move files
find . -name "*.log" -exec mv {} logs/ \;


Moves all .log files to logs folder.

# 15. Copy file permissions from one file to another
chmod --reference=config1.yaml config2.yaml

=====>> EXTRA POWER COMMANDS YOU WON’T FIND IN BASICS <<===============
⭐ 16. Show file sizes in human readable format
du -sh *


Useful to check which folder is heavy.

⭐ 17. Show biggest files in current directory
du -sh * | sort -hr | head

⭐ 18. Show disk usage
df -h

⭐ 19. Find large files above 1 GB
find / -type f -size +1G

⭐ 20. Rename multiple files together
rename 's/.txt/.bak/' *.txt


Changes .txt → .bak

⭐ 21. Show last modified times
stat file.txt

⭐ 22. Secure delete a file
shred -u secret.txt


Overwrites file so recovery is impossible.

⭐ 23. Search multiple keywords in file
grep -E "error|fail|critical" app.log

⭐ 24. Copy files across servers
scp file.txt user@server:/path/

⭐ 25. Sync folders (backup/production mirroring)
rsync -avz source/ destination/

⭐ 26. Move everything EXCEPT certain files
rsync -av --exclude="*.png" ./ /backup/

⭐ 27. Check file type
file unknownfile


Shows whether it's binary, text, script, etc.

⭐ 28. View file permissions in numeric format
stat -c "%a %n" *

⭐ 29. Open file with default application
xdg-open file.pdf

⭐ 30. Give temporary sudo permission to edit a system file
sudo -E vim /etc/hosts
